{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Meatballs","content":["Place 150 g part-frozen pork tenderloin in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining 200 g part-frozen pork tenderloin in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr> . Add to bowl and set aside.","Place garlic, coriander, spring onions and carrot in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sesame oil, reserved minced pork, egg, Chinese five spice, soy sauce, chilli (if using), salt and pepper then mix <nobr>30 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr> while stirring with spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid. Grease Varoma dish with oil.","Using wet hands, form 1 heaped tablespoon of mixture into a golf ball sized ball and place in prepared Varoma dish. Repeat with remaining mixture to form 18 balls. Brush balls with water then set dish aside."]},{"title":"Vegetables and Noodles","content":["Place stock cubes and water in mixing bowl then bring to the boil <nobr>8 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Place covered Varoma into position and steam <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, prepare carrot and courgette in ribbons, slice pepper and drain bamboo shoots. Mix together then transfer to Varoma tray.","Insert Varoma tray then cover Varoma and steam <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Set Varoma aside.","Place a large bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in noodles. Remove bowl then pour cooking water onto noodles and allow to stand until soft (approx. 3 minutes). Using tongs, transfer noodles to a serving dish and toss with steamed vegetables. Arrange meatballs on top and sprinkle with coriander. Serve warm with sauce of choice, such as soy sauce (see tip)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Meatballs","content":["350 g pork tenderloin, cut in 3 cm slices then frozen for 30 minutes","1 garlic clove","3 sprigs fresh coriander","2 spring onions, cut in lengths (2 cm) (approx. 30 g)","1 carrot, cut in pieces (approx. 100 g)","10 g toasted sesame oil, plus extra for greasing","1 large egg","½ Tbsp Chinese five spice powder","1 Tbsp soy sauce","1 - 2 pinches dried chilli flakes              (optional)","1 pinch fine sea salt, or to taste","3 pinches ground pepper, or to taste","water, for brushing"]},{"title":"Vegetables and Noodles","content":["2 vegetable stock cubes (each for 0.5 l)","1000 g water","1 carrot (approx. 100 g)","1 courgette (approx. 100 g)","1 pepper (approx. 120 g)","50 g tinned bamboo shoots, drained","250 g egg noodles, dried, fine","4 sprigs coriander leaves, as garnish"]}],"id":"r102882","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-I5iylMTufiY\/XZQx2_ojh6I\/AAAAAAAAcyI\/ePAjDGMbaDYrpKgixzA8DsB4xqHV_unsACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_zyrxfpeyy3WNqdLo.png","title":"Oriental Pork Meatballs with Noodles","publishedAt":"2017-03-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"25.5 g","fat":"10.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"23 g","calories":"1210 kJ \/ 289 kcal"},"usefulItems":"tongs, bowl, pastry brush, vegetable peeler, serving bowl, large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["To give finished meatballs a crispy coating, finish off by frying in an oiled pan until lightly browned on all sides.","Drizzle dish with some of the fragrant cooking water instead of a sauce, if desired.<br>"],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h","4 portions"]}